<root><template><title>RV</title><part><name>type</name>=<value>command

</value></part><part><name>game1</name>=<value> arma3

</value></part><part><name>version1</name>=<value> 2.02

</value></part><part><name>gr1</name>=<value> HashMap

</value></part><part><name>descr</name>=<value> Merges two [[HashMap]]s.

</value></part><part><name>s1</name>=<value> hashMap1 [[merge]] hashMap2

</value></part><part><name>p1</name>=<value> hashMap1: [[HashMap]] - This HashMap will be modified

</value></part><part><name>p2</name>=<value> hashMap2: [[HashMap]] - All key-value pairs from this HashMap are added to ''hashMap1''. If a key from ''hashMap2'' already exists in ''hashMap1'', then its value is overwritten with the corresponding value from ''hashMap2''

</value></part><part><name>r1</name>=<value> [[Nothing]]

</value></part><part><name>s2</name>=<value> hashMap1 [[merge]] [hashMap2, overwriteExisting]

</value></part><part><name>p21</name>=<value> hashMap1: [[HashMap]] - This HashMap will be modified

</value></part><part><name>p22</name>=<value> hashMap2: [[HashMap]] - All key-value pairs from this HashMap are added to ''hashMap1''

</value></part><part><name>p23</name>=<value> overwriteExisting (Optional, default: [[false]]): [[Boolean]] - If [[true]], keys from ''hashMap1'' that also exist in ''hashMap2'' are overwritten. When set to [[true]], merging is faster

</value></part><part><name>r2</name>=<value> [[Nothing]]

</value></part><part><name>x1</name>=<value> <code>_hashMap [[merge]] _otherHashMap;</code>

</value></part><part><name>seealso</name>=<value> [[insert]] [[set]]
</value></part></template></root>
